column5: Well it was such a nice looking day I had to take Jade out for some musky hunting we hit the launch around 9:30 I missed one fish casting. There was not much action where we were so we headed east on the lake over to another spot I like and sure enough 15 min in Jade landed her first of the day about 30" heck she even thought it was to small for a pic. I just set the lines and one of them went off I got to see the fish it was a fat mid 40's fish that broke the 50lbs PP it was frayed so I think I have a bad guide on that rod I will look at it later. we were heading back to the launch and made one more turn and she landed this one what a great day with my bast fishing partner.
Nice Mike !! No matter how big they are, Musky's are beautiful fish.
Gotta love a kid who doesn't want a picture of a 30! She knows there are better ones ahead
NIce looking ski. Thanks for sharing.
A 30" fish thats " to small for a picture ". What kind of musky snob are you raising. Nice fish and report Mike. Congrats to the young lady.
Thanks for the tale Mike & congrats to Jade, she's having a great year with the muskies.

Thanks all I just love to get out with Jade and it sure did put a smile on my face more of laughter when she did not want a pic then being proud as Rizzo was saying she commented that we need a bigger one, she is on the hunt for her 50" We did some casting yesterday but it did not pan out next season she will start using a  bait caster it should make casting a bit more easier for her.
Awesome Mike, good on ya  Nice fish
PP Power Pro the rods are half switched over to 100lbs PP now and the rest over the winter.
Great day there ...   as this season is quickly winding down.
Great father daughter team work Mike Congrats to Jade on the beauty ski Thanks for sharing Leechman
